User Interface Requirements
 
/signup
This page is used to make an account, enter the chosen email and password then press the signup button below.

 
/login
This page is used to login into your account, enter the corresponding email and password then press the login button below.
 
/profile
This page displays the information pertaining to your account including your email and role which defaults to regular for any new users. The logout link on the bottom left takes you back to the login page, the go to map link to its right takes you to the map. 

 
/admin/dashboard
This page displays information about the accounts registered to the website (only visible to the admin), it shows the number of accounts at the top, and the emails and roles pertaining to all accounts at the bottom.
 
/map
This page shows a map of your area, the similar location button in the top left shows a list of genres between café, restaurant, museum, and park. When one of them is pressed it displays pins across the map pertaining to those types of locations. To the right of it is a logout button when pressed it takes you back to the login page. To save a location you simply press on any location on the map and an option to save it will come up, pressing the show saved location button will bring up the list of saved locations in the top right corner. From there you can hide the list or remove a location from it aswell.
 
/route-shared
This page shows the details of a route that is shared to a user. It lists the name of the route at the very top, followed by who shared it, then a description of the route. It lists the potential stops on the way there aswell as buttons to go back or accept the route.

